  <description type="morphology">Plants small, cespitose, glossy, dark green.  Stems erect, to 0.5 cm.  Leaves crispate when dry, oblong-lanceolate, 2 mm; margins entire distally, erect proximally; apex cucullate to subcucullate.  Specialized asexual reproduction rare, short-uniseriate or branched gemmae, several cells long, on branched axillary filaments.  Seta 1 per perichaetium, 2–3 mm.  Capsule ovoid, 0.75–1 mm, smooth or wrinkled when dry; peristome teeth perforate but mostly not divided, densely papillose.  Calyptra lobes about one third length of calyptra.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Capsules mature Sep–Jun.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Acidic and calcareous rocks, soil, very rarely tree bark, open forests;</description>
